Package com.intellij.execution.process

Class ProcessOutputType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.util.Key<java.lang.Object>
      • com.intellij.execution.process.ProcessOutputType

  • public class ProcessOutputType
extends Key<java.lang.Object>
    Represents a stream (stdout/stderr/system) output type. It can be a base output type or a colored output type. Base stdout/stderr output types are constants: ProcessOutputTypes.STDOUT, ProcessOutputTypes.STDERR and ProcessOutputTypes.SYSTEM.
    A colored stdout/stderr output type corresponds to an unique ANSI color attributes info passed as name constructor parameter, and base stream output type (stdout/stderr) - streamType parameter.

    Use ConsoleViewContentType.getConsoleViewType(com.intellij.openapi.util.Key) to get TextAttributes for an instance of this class.

    See Also:
    ColoredOutputTypeRegistry, ConsoleViewContentType.registerNewConsoleViewType(com.intellij.openapi.util.Key, com.intellij.openapi.editor.colors.TextAttributesKey)

    • Field Detail

      • SYSTEM

        public static final ProcessOutputType SYSTEM

      • STDOUT

        public static final ProcessOutputType STDOUT
        Base type for data from process standard output stream.

        Colored texts from stdout are represented by different instances of ProcessOutputType having ProcessOutputType.STDOUT base type: 

         coloredStdoutType.getBaseOutputType() == ProcessOutputType.STDOUT

        Thus to check whether a process output type is from stdout: 

         ProcessOutputType.isStdout(key)
        instead of 
         ProcessOutputType.STDOUT.equals(key) or ProcessOutputType.STDOUT == key

      • STDERR

        public static final ProcessOutputType STDERR
        Base type for data from process standard error stream.

        Colored texts from stderr are represented by different instances of ProcessOutputType having ProcessOutputType.STDERR base type: 

         coloredStderrType.getBaseOutputType() == ProcessOutputType.STDERR

        Thus to check whether a process output type is from stderr: 

         ProcessOutputType.isStderr(key)
        instead of 
         ProcessOutputType.STDERR.equals(key) or ProcessOutputType.STDERR == key
